The <b>Cozumel Vireo</b> (<i>Vireo bairdi</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the family <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vireonidae" title="Vireonidae" class="mw-redirect">Vireonidae</a>. It is <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endemism" title="Endemism">endemic</a> to the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexican</a> island of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cozumel" title="Cozumel">Cozumel</a> off the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yucat%C3%A1n_Peninsula" title="Yucatán Peninsula">Yucatán Peninsula</a>. Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a> and heavily degraded former forest.
